{"name":"Benzoic acid","desc":"Benzoic acid /bɛnˈzoʊ.ɪk/, C7H6O2 (or C6H5COOH), is a colorless crystalline solid and a simple aromatic carboxylic acid. The name is derived from gum benzoin, which was for a long time its only known source. Benzoic acid occurs naturally in many plants and it serves as an intermediate in the biosynthesis of many secondary metabolites. Salts of benzoic acid are used as food preservatives and benzoic acid is an important precursor for the industrial synthesis of many other organic substances. The salts and esters of benzoic acid are known as benzoates /ˈbɛnzoʊ.eɪt/.","images":[{"alt":"Skeletal formula","src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Benzoes%C3%A4ure.svg/100px-Benzoes%C3%A4ure.svg.png"},{"alt":"Benzoic acid crystals","src":"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Benzoid_acid.jpg/200px-Benzoid_acid.jpg"}],"link":"/wiki/Benzoic_acid","":"","Preferred IUPAC name[1]":"Benzoic acid[1]\nBenzoic acid[1]","Systematic IUPAC name":"Benzenecarboxylic acid\nBenzenecarboxylic acid","E210":"Carboxybenzene; E210; Dracylic acid; Phenylmethanoic acid","CAS Number":"65-85-0 Y","3D model (JSmol)":"Interactive image\nInteractive image","3DMet":"B00053","Beilstein Reference":"636131","ChEBI":"CHEBI:30746 Y","ChemSpider":"238 Y","DrugBank":"DB03793 Y","ECHA InfoCard":"100.000.562","EC Number":"200-618-2","E number":"E210 (preservatives)","Gmelin Reference":"2946","KEGG":"D00038 Y","MeSH":"benzoic+acid","PubChem CID":"243","RTECS number":"DG0875000","UNII":"8SKN0B0MIM Y","Chemical formula":"<span title=\"Carbon\">C</span><sub>7</sub><span title=\"Hydrogen\">H</span><sub>6</sub><span title=\"Oxygen\">O</span><sub>2</sub>","Molar mass":"122.12 g·mol−1","Appearance":"Colorless crystalline solid","Odor":"faint, pleasant odor","Density":"1.2659 g/cm<sup>3</sup> (15 &#xB0;C)<br>\n1.0749 g/cm<sup>3</sup> (130 &#xB0;C)<sup id=\"cite_ref-chemister_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-chemister-2\">[2]</a></sup>","Meltin